dct_alternative_sm: Rand McNally standard map of California
Rand McNally main highway map of California
dct_description_sm: Shows railways, steamship lines, towns, counties and national parks; map on verso shows various highways--Lincoln Highway, Roosevelt National Highway, Midland Trail, etc.
"The Rand McNally new commercial atlas map of California."
Relief shown by hachures and spot heights.
Shows railways, steamship lines, towns, counties and national parks.
Includes indexes and insets of Los Angeles, San Diego and San Francisco Bay area.
At head of title: Rand McNally.
On verso: Rand McNally main highway map of California, with index and insets of Los Angeles, San Diego and San Francisco Bay Area.
Title of accompanying text, dated 1924: California, Rand McNally indexed pocket map, tourists' and shippers' guide.
